& git commit -m \\\"feat(prompt-00): project charter\\\"'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"[yolopilot-init-00-project-charter e66c606] feat(prompt-00): project charter\\n 3 files changed, 260 insertions(+)\\n create mode 100644 README.md\\n create mode 100644 docs/architecture-overview.md\\n create mode 100644 docs/product-brief.md\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:59:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_32\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Added the project charter docs at [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md), [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md), and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md). The README now calls out the past-sessions-first home screen early, lists the full staged workflow in order, and documents the fixed stack and local development expectations. The architecture note records the backend-only Gemini boundary and the requirement for resumable server-side composition/audio jobs.\\n\\nVerification was docs-focused: I manually reviewed all three files, ran a Python acceptance check covering file presence, first-screen wording, ordered workflow, fixed stack documentation, backend Gemini rationale, resumable jobs rationale, and sessions-home coverage in the product brief, and ran `git diff --check`, which passed. No tests, builds, browser checks, or screenshots were applicable because this task was documentation-only.\\n\\nI created the requested checkpoint commit `feat(prompt-00): project charter`, and the required reviewer summary file was written last at [prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md).\"}}\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:60:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_15\",\"type\":\"todo_list\",\"items\":[{\"text\":\"Draft top-level README with product vision, ordered workflow, fixed technology decisions, and local development expectations\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Add docs/product-brief.md and docs/architecture-overview.md aligned to the prompt and current scaffold\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Verify content against acceptance criteria, commit a checkpoint, and write prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md as the final action\",\"completed\":false}]}}\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md:28:  - workflow stage changes\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md:100:- affected `workflow_stage_states.last_event_id` pointers are updated so snapshots can explain why a stage is in its current state\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md:155:    selection_id=\"genre-1\",\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md:169:    detail=\"Accepted a revised brief.\",\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md:280:- `workflow_stage_states.last_event_id`\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:17:  genre_id: string\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:28:  genre_id?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:29:  genre_slug?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:30:  genre_label?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:35:  tone_profile_id?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:36:  tone_profile_slug?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:37:  tone_profile_label?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:47:  return getJson<GenreCatalogEntry[]>('/api/v1/catalog/genres')\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:50:export function fetchToneCatalogForGenre(genreSlug: string) {\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:52:    `/api/v1/catalog/genres/${encodeURIComponent(genreSlug)}/tones`,\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:61:    `/api/v1/sessions/${sessionId}/selections/genre`,\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:71:    `/api/v1/sessions/${sessionId}/selections/tone`,\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md:24:- The architecture notes reflect the actual product brief instead of a generic app template.\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1323:            \"genre\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1324:            \"tone\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1325:            \"brief\",\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:10:function getToastTone(tone: AppShellToast['tone']) {\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:11:  if (tone === 'success') {\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:15:  if (tone === 'warning') {\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:19:  if (tone === 'danger') {\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:42:            className={`toast-region__item toast-region__item--${toast.tone}`}\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/ToastRegion.tsx:46:                <Badge tone={getToastTone(toast.tone)}>{toast.title}</Badge>\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:32:  selected_genre?: SessionCatalogSelection | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:33:  selected_tone_profile?: SessionCatalogSelection | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:53:  raw_brief: string\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:256:  story_brief?: StoryBriefView | null\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:26:    get_workflow_stage_definition,\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:164:            \"Please rephrase the change you want, like tone, runtime, beats, or audio settings.\"\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:175:    stage_definition = get_workflow_stage_definition(snapshot.current_stage)\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:215:            stage_label = get_workflow_stage_definition(target_stage).label\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:224:            \"I can queue a fresh set of pitch options from the current bedtime brief.\"\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:257:    stage_definition = get_workflow_stage_definition(snapshot.current_stage)\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:269:    if snapshot.selected_genre is not None:\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:270:        plan_parts.append(snapshot.selected_genre.label)\nbackend/app/services/intent_parser.py:271:    if snapshot.selected_tone_profile is not None:\nbacke