{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml exec -T browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({ executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH, headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'] });\ntry {\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\n  await page.setViewport({ width: 1440, height: 900 });\n  await page.goto('http://frontend:8566/sessions/c6275973-e59a-4862-ad86-350cafc69585', { waitUntil: 'networkidle2', timeout: 15000 });\n  console.log(await page.evaluate(() => document.body.innerText));\n} finally {\n  await browser.close();\n}\nEOF\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "Skip to main content\n\nBEDTIME STORY STUDIO\n\nStoryteller\nSessions\nWorkspace\n\nResume existing stories or open a session workspace when you are ready to continue.\n\nCONNECTION\n\nBackend reachability\nLast checked 2:57 AM.\nOnline\nCheck again\n\nThe app shell is connected to FastAPI through the Vite development proxy.\n\nHello from FastAPI!\n\nSESSION WORKSPACE\n\nPrompt 42 Visual QA\n\nChat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right canvas reserved for structured editing.\n\nCurrent stage\nStory brief\nSave status\nSaved Apr 2, 2:55 AM\nSession ID\nc6275973-e59a-4862-ad86-350cafc69585\nLive updates\nIdle\n\nSet VITE_SESSION_EVENTS_WS_URL to enable live updates.\n\nIn progress\nReturn home\nLive feed idle\nIn progress\n\nThe workspace is running from the durable snapshot only. Configure the websocket endpoint to start session-scoped live updates.\n\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed idle\n\nReady for notes, approvals, and stage edits from the conversation lane.\n\nSystem\nApr 2, 2:55 AM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Story brief.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 2:55 AM\n\nSelected genre: Quest Fantasy\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 2:55 AM\n\nSelected tone: Hushed Wonder\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nReady\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nPress Enter to send. Press Shift+Enter for a new line. Try /next-stage, /plan.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nQueued\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nCapture the free-form story brief\n\nThis stage will gather the raw bedtime-story idea, clarifications from chat, and the normalized planning summary that later stages rely on.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\n\nThe route and the durable session stage are aligned. Live editors and job views can mount here later without changing the URL pattern.\n\nCurrent brief\n\nBrief not saved yet\n\nThis is the durable bedtime prompt that later pitch generation will inherit.\n\nUnsaved\n\nSpecificity cues\n\nOptional cue fields are still open\n\nOnly the story idea is required. The optional cues stay lightweight so the user can be specific without filling a rigid questionnaire.\n\nQuest Fantasy\nHushed Wonder\n\nNext step\n\nSave to unlock pitches\n\nSave the brief once it feels right, then move into pitch generation.\n\nPreview pitches\nKeep the brief open-ended, not rigid\n\nStart with one or two natural sentences. Use the optional fields only when they add helpful specificity for later pitch generation.\n\nFree-form bedtime brief\n\nCapture the story in natural language first, then add optional cues only if they will sharpen later pitch generation.\n\nRequired\nStory idea\n\nOne or two vivid sentences is enough. Write this the way you would explain the story idea to a calm human collaborator.\n\nStart with the bedtime story idea in your own words.\n\nDesired themes\n\nThemes can stay broad or emotional: belonging, gentle courage, grief repair, wonder, and so on.\n\nKey images\n\nCall out the images or motifs you want the story to keep returning to.\n\nTarget audience notes\n\nAudience notes can cover age, sensitivity, family context, or read-aloud preferences.\n\nMust-have elements\n\nUse this for non-negotiables: a calm ending, a dragon friend, a lighthouse, or any image that must appear.\n\nSave brief\nReset\n\nNot saved yet\n\nPlanner preview\n\nBrief not saved yet\n\nThis is the compiled prompt text that the backend persists for downstream planning.\n\nDraft only\nNot saved yet\nSTORY LANE\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\nOPTIONAL CUES FILLED\n0\n\nThe compiled prompt preview will appear here as the brief takes shape.\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n2 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Story brief with 20% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\n\nThe structured brief, pitch, and beat choices will accumulate here as the session advances.\n\nProduction\n\nStory brief\n\nComposition and audio controls will take over this area once the planning stages are complete.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml exec -T browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({ executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH, headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'] });\ntry {\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\n  await page.setViewport({ width: 1440, height: 900 });\n  await page.goto('http://frontend:8566/sessions/c6275973-e59a-4862-ad86-350cafc69585', { waitUntil: 'networkidle2', timeout: 15000 });\n  console.log(await page.evaluate(() => document.body.innerText));\n} finally {\n  await browser.close();\n}\nEOF\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_256", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 485, "prompt_index": 43, "prompt_name": "42 \u2014 Story Setup Brief Form", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T19:57:47-07:00"}
{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "I confirmed the brief stage is rendering correctly inside the compose network; the earlier screenshot script failure was a shell-quoting issue from `zsh` history expansion, not a UI problem. I\u2019m rerunning the capture with history expansi...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_257", "text": "I confirmed the brief stage is rendering correctly inside the compose network; the earlier screenshot script failure was a shell-quoting issue from `zsh` history expansion, not a UI problem. I\u2019m rerunning the capture with history expansion disabled so I can produce the actual desktop/mobile artifacts and the post-save confirmation shot.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 486, "prompt_index": 43, "prompt_name": "42 \u2014 Story Setup Brief Form", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T19:57:56-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"set +H\nSESSION_ID=c6275973-e59a-4862-ad86-350cafc69585 docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml exec -T browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\nimport process from 'node:process';\n\nconst baseUrl = process.env.TARGET_BASE_URL;\nconst sessionId = process.env.SESSION_ID;\nconst desktopPath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-desktop.png';\nconst mobilePath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-mobile.png';\nconst savePath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-after-save.png';\n\nasync function waitForText(page, text) {\n  await page.waitForFunction(\n    (expectedText) => document.body?.innerText.includes(expectedText),\n    { timeout: 15000 },\n    text,\n  );\n}\n\nasync function delay(ms) {\n  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nasync function setTextAreaByLabel(page, labelText, value) {\n  const updated = await page.evaluate((expectedLabel, nextValue) => {\n    const labels = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('label'));\n    const label = labels.find(\n      (entry) => entry.textContent?.trim() === expectedLabel,\n    );\n    const id = label?.getAttribute('for');\n    const element = id ? document.getElementById(id) : null;\n\n    if (\"'!(element instanceof HTMLTextAreaElement)) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    element.focus();\n    element.value = nextValue;\n    element.dispatchEvent(new Event('\"'input', { bubbles: true }));\n    element.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));\n    return true;\n  }, labelText, value);\n\n  if (\"'!updated) {\n    throw new Error(`Unable to find textarea labelled ${labelText}`);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function clickButtonByText(page, text) {\n  const clicked = await page.evaluate((expectedText) => {\n    const buttons = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('\"'button'));\n    const button = buttons.find(\n      (entry) => entry.textContent?.trim() === expectedText,\n    );\n\n    if (\"'!(button instanceof HTMLButtonElement)) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    button.click();\n    return true;\n  }, text);\n\n  if (!clicked) {\n    throw new Error(`Unable to find button ${text}`);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function openBriefPage(page, viewport) {\n  await page.setViewport(viewport);\n  await page.goto(`${baseUrl}/sessions/${sessionId}`, {\n    waitUntil: '\"'networkidle2',\n    timeout: 15000,\n  });\n  await waitForText(page, 'Capture the free-form story brief');\n  await waitForText(page, 'Story idea');\n}\n\nasync function fillBrief(page) {\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Story idea',\n    'A sleepy child follows floating lanterns across a moonlit harbor to help an otter guardian guide them home.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Desired themes',\n    'Gentle courage, belonging, and a calm return home.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Key images',\n    'Floating lanterns, still water, and a warm harbor light.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Target audience notes',\n    'For a sensitive five-year-old who likes rescue stories without villains.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Must-have elements',\n    'An otter friend and a restful final page.',\n  );\n  await delay(300);\n}\n\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({\n  executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH,\n  headless: true,\n  args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'],\n});\n\ntry {\n  const desktopPage = await browser.newPage();\n  await openBriefPage(desktopPage, { width: 1440, height: 900 });\n  await fillBrief(desktopPage);\n  await desktopPage.screenshot({ path: desktopPath, fullPage: false });\n\n  const mobilePage = await browser.newPage();\n  await openBriefPage(mobilePage, { width: 430, height: 932 });\n  await fillBrief(mobilePage);\n  await mobilePage.screenshot({ path: mobilePath, fullPage: false });\n  await mobilePage.close();\n\n  await clickButtonByText(desktopPage, 'Save brief');\n  await waitForText(desktopPage, 'Review and select story pitches');\n  await desktopPage.screenshot({ path: savePath, fullPage: false });\n  await desktopPage.close();\n\n  console.log(JSON.stringify({ desktopPath, mobilePath, savePath }, null, 2));\n} finally {\n  await browser.close();\n}\nEOF\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"set +H\nSESSION_ID=c6275973-e59a-4862-ad86-350cafc69585 docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml exec -T browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\nimport process from 'node:process';\n\nconst baseUrl = process.env.TARGET_BASE_URL;\nconst sessionId = process.env.SESSION_ID;\nconst desktopPath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-desktop.png';\nconst mobilePath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-mobile.png';\nconst savePath = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-42-story-brief-after-save.png';\n\nasync function waitForText(page, text) {\n  await page.waitForFunction(\n    (expectedText) => document.body?.innerText.includes(expectedText),\n    { timeout: 15000 },\n    text,\n  );\n}\n\nasync function delay(ms) {\n  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nasync function setTextAreaByLabel(page, labelText, value) {\n  const updated = await page.evaluate((expectedLabel, nextValue) => {\n    const labels = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('label'));\n    const label = labels.find(\n      (entry) => entry.textContent?.trim() === expectedLabel,\n    );\n    const id = label?.getAttribute('for');\n    const element = id ? document.getElementById(id) : null;\n\n    if (\"'!(element instanceof HTMLTextAreaElement)) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    element.focus();\n    element.value = nextValue;\n    element.dispatchEvent(new Event('\"'input', { bubbles: true }));\n    element.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));\n    return true;\n  }, labelText, value);\n\n  if (\"'!updated) {\n    throw new Error(`Unable to find textarea labelled ${labelText}`);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function clickButtonByText(page, text) {\n  const clicked = await page.evaluate((expectedText) => {\n    const buttons = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('\"'button'));\n    const button = buttons.find(\n      (entry) => entry.textContent?.trim() === expectedText,\n    );\n\n    if (\"'!(button instanceof HTMLButtonElement)) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    button.click();\n    return true;\n  }, text);\n\n  if (!clicked) {\n    throw new Error(`Unable to find button ${text}`);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function openBriefPage(page, viewport) {\n  await page.setViewport(viewport);\n  await page.goto(`${baseUrl}/sessions/${sessionId}`, {\n    waitUntil: '\"'networkidle2',\n    timeout: 15000,\n  });\n  await waitForText(page, 'Capture the free-form story brief');\n  await waitForText(page, 'Story idea');\n}\n\nasync function fillBrief(page) {\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Story idea',\n    'A sleepy child follows floating lanterns across a moonlit harbor to help an otter guardian guide them home.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Desired themes',\n    'Gentle courage, belonging, and a calm return home.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Key images',\n    'Floating lanterns, still water, and a warm harbor light.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Target audience notes',\n    'For a sensitive five-year-old who likes rescue stories without villains.',\n  );\n  await setTextAreaByLabel(\n    page,\n    'Must-have elements',\n    'An otter friend and a restful final page.',\n  );\n  await delay(300);\n}\n\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({\n  executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH,\n  headless: true,\n  args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-